UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1724
1 to KRS 199.8994. To be eligible for funds, a group or individual shall:
2 1. If a provider or a home, maintain services for infants and toddlers at a
3 ratio established by the Division of Child Care within the cabinet;
4 2. If a provider or a home, maintain and submit accurate and detailed
5 records of care for any child; and
6 3. If a parent, submit records to verify he or she meets the requirements
7 to receive child care subsidy funds under KRS 199.8994; and
8 (h) Establish a standard for how to award a two thousand dollar ($2,000) one
9 (1) time payment per child once a child is designated by the assessment
10 processes as kindergarten ready as follows:
11 1. A full payment to a licensed Type I and Type II child-care center or
12 cabinet-regulated early childhood education provider, certified child-
13 care home, and registered provider who meets the requirements of
14 paragraph (g) of this subsection if the kindergarten-ready child
15 received full-time services from the center or provider the two (2) years
16 prior to the assessment;
17 2. A full payment to a single or married parent who meets the
18 requirements of paragraph (g) of this subsection if the kindergarten-
19 ready child was cared for in the home the two (2) years prior to the
20 assessment, regardless of the utilization of a babysitter;
21 3. A full payment to a licensed Type I and Type II child-care center or
22 cabinet-regulated early childhood education provider, certified child-
23 care home, and registered provider who meets the requirements of
24 paragraph (g) of this subsection if the child cannot be properly
25 assessed as a kindergarten-ready child because of a formal diagnosis
26 with a disability and the child received full-time services from the
27 provider the two (2) years prior to the assessment;
Page 3 of 5
