UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1724
1 4. A half payment to a licensed Type I and Type II child-care center or
2 cabinet-regulated early childhood education provider, certified child-
3 care home, and registered provider who meets the requirements of
4 paragraph (g) of this subsection if the kindergarten-ready child
5 received half-day services from the center and attended public
6 preschool the two (2) years prior to the assessment; and
7 5. Split payments may be granted to individuals or entities based on who
8 provided full-time services or cared for the child in the two (2) years
9 prior to the assessment.
10 (4) By October 1, 2029, the university shall submit a report to the cabinet and the
11 Legislative Research Commission for referral to the Interim Joint Committees on
12 Families and Children, Education, and Appropriations and Revenue that:
13 (a) Details the findings of the pilot program;
14 (b) If the pilot program proves successful:
15 1. Identifies specific mechanisms for change, including but not limited to
16 educational curricula and family practices to best prepare preschool-
17 age children for kindergarten readiness;
18 2. Includes recommendations based on the pilot program's results for
19 optimizing performance-based child care incentives in the
20 Commonwealth; and
21 3. Includes recommendations and potential obstacles for implementing
22 the program at scale;
23 (c) Details the assessment processes used to determine kindergarten readiness;
24 (d) Identifies the rates of kindergarten readiness at the end of the pilot
25 program; and
26 (e) Includes all data generated from the pilot program, which shall be made
27 available for public review and use in accordance with applicable federal,
